Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:32.21,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1528,188)\blur0.25\fs33\fnGeorgia\fsp3.0\c&HF8CC9E&\t(2529,5824,\c&HFAFBFA&)\pos(326,245)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.98,0:01:32.98,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(390,269)}Episode 30: The Hero of the South
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.34,0:01:39.74,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Will you polish the statue of the hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:42.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What's the reward?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.89,0:01:47.84,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,A spell to scratch the \Nitchy parts on your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.71,0:01:56.72,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin Fabel Village, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.44,0:02:01.47,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing this kind of job again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.28,0:02:05.60,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There are statues of Mr. Himmel \Neverywhere, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.11,0:02:10.04,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Well, odd jobs like these are fun, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:13.09,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get polishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.09,0:02:15.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bronze statue, so we can use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.58,0:02:17.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You won't have anything to do, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.96,0:02:18.67,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.50,0:02:28.37,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, who's this guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.44,0:02:31.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your first time seeing him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:34.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Hero of the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.89,0:02:40.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel was the one who defeated the \NDemon King, but he wasn't the only hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.80,0:02:45.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,All kinds of heroes made the attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.63,0:02:51.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Among them, the Hero of the South \Nwas said to be humanity's strongest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.05,0:02:53.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That seems a bit extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:54.36,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.91,0:02:57.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He was worthy of that title.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.11,0:03:01.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, the greatest \Nthreat to humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:05.36,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,was the Seven Sages of Destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.36,0:03:08.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,who controlled the major regions \Naround the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:14.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We actually only defeated two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:21.33,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Of the remaining five, \Ntwo either fled or went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.60,0:03:23.87,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Like Aura the Guillotine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.46,0:03:28.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hero of the South \Ndefeated the remaining three.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:35.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,His rapid advance was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.14,0:03:40.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In just a year, he annihilated the \NDemon King's front-line troops
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.19,0:03:44.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and reached the northernmost \Nend of the Northern Plateau—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.77,0:03:47.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,the heart of the Demon King's \Nsupply route back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.49,0:03:53.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That was where he was defeated \Nby Schlacht the Omniscient—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.51,0:03:59.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,the Demon King's confidant who could see \N1,000 years into the future with magic—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.33,0:04:03.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and the combined forces \Nof all Seven Sages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:06.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,All Seven Sages...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.50,0:04:08.26,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.93,0:04:13.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hero of the South still managed \Nto defeat three of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.78,0:04:17.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and he and Schlacht the \NOmniscient slew each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.85,0:04:28.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That battle liberated many people \Nin this region from the Seven Sages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:32.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The people here are devoted \Nto the Hero of the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:37.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Since his body was never found,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.43,0:04:44.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,legends claim he's still fighting \NSchlacht the Omniscient to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.62,0:04:49.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Though, given that the demons he \Nfought had a taste for human flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.79,0:04:52.72,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I think he was actually just eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:58.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we get this cleaned up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.56,0:05:05.54,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:08.74,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.03,0:05:13.04,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,So you refused after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.52,0:05:18.03,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, I don't know the \Nright words to convince you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:24.54,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You speak like you already \Nknew this would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:28.54,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.27,0:05:35.05,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,But I suppose I can tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.46,0:05:43.16,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you learn my secret, \Nyou'll never tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.42,0:05:47.19,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,So I shall tell you, and only you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.69,0:05:51.55,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,the reason I am humanity's \Nstrongest hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.43,0:05:57.13,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I can see the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.00,0:06:01.84,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. That's impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.03,0:06:06.10,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.49,0:06:11.75,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that. I just don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:19.07,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Then perhaps this \Nwill pique your interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.23,0:06:23.20,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You know of the Seven Sages \Nof Destruction, do you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.13,0:06:34.56,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,One year from now in the Northern Plateau,\NI will be defeated and slain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:39.45,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,by Schlacht the Omniscient \Nand the Seven Sages.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.65,0:07:14.83,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I will die without achieving my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.03,0:07:22.20,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Don't feel sorry for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:29.20,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you accompanied me, \Nmy fate would not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:32.22,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,But soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.03,0:07:36.32,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,a young hero will visit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.13,0:07:44.20,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to admit it, but he is the one \Nwho will save the world, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.35,0:07:50.81,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You will travel with that young man's \Nparty and defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:53.75,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I really can't see that happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.61,0:07:56.62,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,You'll understand once you meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.27,0:08:00.03,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,He'll change your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:07.48,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.82,0:08:15.58,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,May I ask you for one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.97,0:08:16.77,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.77,0:08:21.93,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,When you meet that young man, \Ntell him this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.35,0:08:40.03,FlashbackItalics,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.71,0:08:46.45,FlashbackItalics,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I will clear a path for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.64,0:08:57.42,Flashback,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I, humanity's strongest hero: \Nthe Hero of the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.71,0:09:05.66,FlashbackItalics,HERO OF THE SOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,Even if my accomplishments should \Nbe buried in the shadows of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.54,0:09:12.14,Default,CHILDREN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.14,0:09:13.52,Default,CHILDREN,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.39,0:09:21.69,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,Some future sight you had.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:26.09,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,The people here remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.66,0:09:29.15,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,History hasn't forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:35.01,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin Graf Dach's domain, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.15,0:09:38.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since we \Nwere last in a big city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.24,0:09:41.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving as soon as \Nwe're done resupplying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.08,0:09:43.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.53,0:09:45.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We're not gonna take our time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.14,0:09:51.12,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, they've got magic shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.66,0:09:55.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know, Stark? Time is finite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:56.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.60,0:10:22.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:27.14,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why don't we at least \Nget something nice to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.51,0:10:34.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You know we don't have the money \Nto spare for that, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.77,0:10:36.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.83,0:10:38.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.52,0:10:41.98,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's been acting strange \Nthis whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.13,0:10:49.61,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Normally she thinks nothing of staying \Nin a big city for a few months.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.55,0:10:53.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.65,0:10:56.75,Default,SERVANT,0000,0000,0000,,You must be Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.34,0:11:01.22,Default,SERVANT,0000,0000,0000,,My lord would like to \Ninvite you to dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.84,0:11:04.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.42,0:11:12.47,Default,SERVANT,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren was a member of the party \Nof heroes that saved this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.30,0:11:15.82,Default,SERVANT,0000,0000,0000,,My lord wishes to thank you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:30.93,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.17,0:11:35.92,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the invitation, Graf Dach.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.51,0:11:39.29,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,She looks really unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:44.17,Default,DACH,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, thank you for \Nhelping my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:46.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.76,0:11:50.46,Default,DACH,0000,0000,0000,,Straight to the point. I appreciate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.46,0:11:55.75,Default,DACH,0000,0000,0000,,My family's treasured heirloom \Nsword was stolen by a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.12,0:11:58.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was stolen again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.75,0:11:59.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,"Again"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.93,0:12:03.53,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was stolen from his \Ngreat-grandfather, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.41,0:12:06.06,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,How does that keep happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.66,0:12:09.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:12.53,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like a grimoire as a reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.16,0:12:17.91,Default,DACH,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be counting on you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.60,0:12:26.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, a lot of nobles in \Nthe northern lands are pushy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:31.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but this family in particular \Nmakes unreasonable demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.31,0:12:36.42,Flashback,GREAT-GRANDFATHER DACH,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't get my sword back, \NI'll throw you into the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.42,0:12:37.59,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:39.36,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about tyrannical.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.58,0:12:44.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,At least they know which way \Nthe demon fled this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.86,0:12:46.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's better than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.31,0:12:53.37,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a real ordeal looking for it \Nwith no leads at all last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.07,0:13:00.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, we found the sword \Nat the top of the Schwer Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.03,0:13:03.76,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.14,0:13:07.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But why would the demons \Nkeep stealing this sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.26,0:13:14.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The Dach family's heirloom sword \Noriginally belonged to a famous demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.37,0:13:18.66,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It must possess some appeal \Nonly demons understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.13,0:13:22.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm surprised \Nyou accepted this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:25.23,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd turn it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.24,0:13:28.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.27,0:13:32.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel brought back that \Nheirloom sword once already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.69,0:13:37.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd refused, his efforts \Nwould've been for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.62,0:13:42.27,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Himmel wouldn't \Nabandon someone in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:32.64,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This village...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.48,0:14:35.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's in ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.16,0:14:39.77,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:47.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.73,0:14:59.21,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you from this village?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:02.86,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm a traveling priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.86,0:15:04.23,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:06.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We're adventurers passing through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.51,0:15:14.61,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,This village was destroyed \Nby the sword demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.46,0:15:19.56,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,I was mourning the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.98,0:15:22.71,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The sword demon...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.79,0:15:26.66,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably the demon we're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.63,0:15:31.23,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,Countless villages have been \Ndestroyed by the sword demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.13,0:15:35.05,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,There have been no survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.13,0:15:37.27,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,How awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.23,0:15:40.25,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.64,0:15:44.07,Default,PRIEST,0000,0000,0000,,will you offer a prayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.34,0:15:53.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.60,0:15:57.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. \NThere are no bodies buried here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.07,0:15:59.19,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.59,0:16:03.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because that priest is the sword demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.80,0:16:06.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There are no corpses left, are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:09.81,Default,SWORD DEMON,0000,0000,0000,,I killed them so I could eat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.56,0:16:15.22,Default,SWORD DEMON,0000,0000,0000,,I had to in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:20.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you can eat things \Nother than humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:25.95,Default,SWORD DEMON,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that a reason not to eat humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.14,0:16:29.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking to it is a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:34.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:49.88,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,It's quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.62,0:17:01.87,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.29,0:17:04.79,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This is what front-liners are for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.84,0:17:29.64,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.64,0:17:31.73,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This was an awful job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:34.62,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,But we got to defeat a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.18,0:17:47.70,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes difficult jobs like these \Nultimately help lots of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.82,0:17:54.92,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I never abandon \Nsomeone in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.92,0:18:01.96,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You just like taking on difficult jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.25,0:18:04.55,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,The challenge is what makes it exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:07.00,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:13.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Good job, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.75,0:18:26.37,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you get violent \Nall of a sudden, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.93,0:18:29.46,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because you were about to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.70,0:18:33.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was all I could do in the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.95,0:18:44.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,People close their eyes to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.66,0:18:50.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That demon must have been taking \Nadvantage of that to kill travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:11.87,Default,DACH,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for returning my treasured \Nheirloom sword, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.20,0:19:15.87,Default,DACH,0000,0000,0000,,Now this city is safe again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.63,0:19:24.72,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go shopping. \NCould you drop us off at the marketplace?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:26.25,Default,SERVANT,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:35.31,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The graf seemed quite happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.31,0:19:37.71,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope it doesn't get stolen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:43.69,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,If the demons find it so appealing, \Nthey'll probably keep trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.69,0:19:44.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they will.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:47.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That was only the second time \Nit was stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:50.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but they've been attacked \Na number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:19:55.56,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,So the demons will keep coming \Nas long as they have that sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.06,0:19:57.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It may be a treasured heirloom,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.83,0:20:00.55,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,but shouldn't they get rid \Nof something so dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.00,0:20:03.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.64,0:20:06.39,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.68,0:20:11.27,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Nobles can be stubborn about \Nletting go of treasures like those.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.08,0:20:18.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There's that, but letting it fall into \Nthe hands of a demon would be worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:24.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Demons can't resist showing off \Nthe power they've acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.81,0:20:31.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the nature of demons?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.55,0:20:36.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A demon went on a rampage \Nthe last time it was stolen, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.87,0:20:41.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It destroyed a town and three villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.27,0:20:43.60,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.73,0:20:49.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but they say \Nthe demon sweet-talked
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.26,0:20:53.27,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,one of the graf's servants into helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.40,0:21:02.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But ever since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.01,0:21:06.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Graf Dach's family has prioritized \Nprotecting the heirloom sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:12.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps now it's not just \Nhis family's mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.03,0:21:14.80,DefaultTop,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,Will I grow up to be strong, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.03,0:21:15.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but that of the whole city.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.80,0:21:15.89,DefaultTop,SOLDIER,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.47,0:21:23.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Did the demon have help stealing \Nthe sword this time, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.92,0:21:25.17,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.17,0:21:32.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But as long as humans know desire, \Ndemons will take advantage of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:39.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Humans also fail to \Nresist their impulses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.50,0:21:46.81,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,If that happens, I hope you'll \Nhelp again, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.44,0:21:49.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That depends on the reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.89,0:21:54.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You'd do it for a grimoire, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.58,0:21:55.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.56,0:22:00.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I got a good one this time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.32,0:22:04.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That's great, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.24,0:22:06.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of spell is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.47,0:22:13.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A spell to turn a red apple \Ninto a green apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:15.59,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.94,0:22:25.07,Credits,CREDITS,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(526,517)\fs10\pos(525,120)}Translation\N{\fs12}Sho Stifler\N\N{\fs10}Editing & Typesetting\N{\fs12}Geoff Mazzolini\N\N{\fs10}Subtitle Timing\N{\fs12}Edgar Cruz\N\N{\fs10}Quality Check\N{\fs12}Alicia Ashby\N\N{\fs10}Translation Check\N{\fs12}Elizabeth Ellis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.09,0:23:52.13,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,This brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.70,0:23:52.12,DefaultOverlap,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'd like to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.60,0:23:52.86,DefaultTop,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You just called me a grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.38,0:23:55.46,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're so inconsiderate, Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.88,0:23:57.18,DefaultTop,OLD WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,You sure love hot springs \Nfor someone so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.55,0:23:55.74,DefaultOverlap,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a truly ridiculous adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.74,0:23:58.81,Default,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You said it'd be quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.36,0:23:58.81,DefaultOverlap,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, there's something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.58,0:24:00.03,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 31\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NSomewhere She'd Like
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.81,0:23:59.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere she'd like.